                                                                  8029 1451
 Nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-3.2.3 Malta                   8029 1451
 (SVN rev.  4976; source rev.  4972)                              8029 1451
 by M.W.Herman et al [EMP,EMP-man].                               8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 EMPIRE dimensions (dimension.h):                                 8029 1451
  NDNUC= 160  NDEXCLUS= 50  NDEX= 241  NDLW= 100                  8029 1451
  LEVCC= 40  NDLV= 40  NDBR= 40  NDMSCS= 4                        8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                8029 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               8029 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               8029 1451
 of important modules and features:                               8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 8029 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      8029 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  8029 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                8029 1451
   and coworkers                                                  8029 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    8029 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          8029 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 8029 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                8029 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       8029 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      8029 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 8029 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                8029 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               8029 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                8029 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   8029 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                8029 1451
   discrete transitions                                           8029 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                8029 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                8029 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               8029 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 8029 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 8029 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              8029 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  8029 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     8029 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 8029 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                8029 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      8029 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   8029 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      8029 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   8029 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  8029 1451
 - generating covariances                                         8029 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 PARAMETERIZATIONS                                                8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 Following models and parameters were used in the                 8029 1451
 current evaluation:                                              8029 1451
                                                                  8029 1451
 Discrete levels were taken from the RIPL-3+                      8029 1451
 library based on the 2015 version of ENSDF.                      8029 1451
 ENDF formatting enabled                                          8029 1451
 Exclusive emission from CN and target enabled                    8029 1451
 Exclusive spectra available for residues distant                 8029 1451
   from CN up to 2 neut. or 2 prot.                               8029 1451
 Target excited to the level # 5                                  8029 1451
 EMPIRE-specific level densities (J>>K aprox.)                    8029 1451
 HRTW width fluctuation correction calculated  up to  3.00 MeV    8029 1451
 Exciton model calculations with code PCROSS                      8029 1451
 Cluster emission in terms of the Iwamoto-Harada model            8029 1451
 Kalbach systematics angular distributions (see RIPL-1)           8029 1451
 Mean free path parameter in PCROSS set to  1.5 (Recomm:~1.5)     8029 1451
 Energy continuum for nucleus 195Pt starts at   0.70              8029 1451
 Energy continuum for nucleus 196Pt starts at   1.68              8029 1451
 Energy continuum for nucleus 193Pt starts at   0.70              8029 1451
 CN anisotropy calculated using Blatt-Biedenharn coefficients     8029 1451
 CN decay and Direct cross sections added incoherently            8029 1451
 Traditional Hauser-Feschbach Tlj_{CC}(E)=Tlj_{GS}(E-Egs)         8029 1451
 E1 strength function set to RIPL MLO1                            8029 1451
 GDR parameters from RIPL/Exp.data+Plujko systematics             8029 1451
 Gamma-transition multipolarity set to    2                       8029 1451
